MethodInfo

                  ClassInfo the_enclosing_class,

Creates a MethodInfo object representing a method with the given parameters.

Parameters:
the_name - The name of the method.
the_enclosing_class - The ClassInfo for the class this method belongs to.
the_declaring_class - The ClassInfo for the class this method is declared in.
the_protection_level - The protection level of the method.
the_parameter_types - The parameter types of the method in order.
the_return_type - The name of the return type of the method.
the_is_constructor - Is the method a constructor?
the_is_static - Is the method static?
the_is_deprecated - Is the method deprecated?

isFactory

public boolean isFactory()
Returns true if this method is a factory method. A factory method is defined as a static method whose return type is the same as the class it belongs to or an abstract parent class thereof.

Returns:
True if this method is a factory. False otherwise.

isTestable

public boolean isTestable()
Returns whether or not this method is testable. A method is testable if and only if it a) is not a constructor of an abstract class, b)has a non-private protection level, and c) is not (and does not override) one of the following methods from java.lang.Object: finalize, getClass, notify, notifyAll, wait.

Returns:
True if this method is testable. False otherwise.
